deposit_type_candidate.observed_name:
Skarn tungsten 
 
 The Fostung tungsten deposit is described as a skarn type, tungsten deposit. Skarn deposits are typically associated with the alteration of carbonate rocks when they come into contact with igneous intrusions. This is consistent with the geological description stating that the tungsten mineralization is found within calcareous siltstone and associated with garnet and pyroxene assemblages.
